description: For sale: $429,900. Simply stunning home on McKinney Lake in the Knollwood neighborhood known for its large wooded lots, beautiful homes and fantastic location in NW Grand Rapids. This home's quality is apparent from the moment you step into the soaring two story foyer that leads to an expansive floor plan. The heart of a home is the kitchen and this one does not disappoint with cherry cabinetry, center island, granite counters, brick faced 2-sided fireplace and large breakfast nook. The main floor also offers an additional dining room, 1/2 bath, laundry, living room and inviting sun room. Upstairs you'll find 4 bdrms, master suite with spa feel bath, a full bath & views of woods or water from every window. Rec room, lots of storage and two bonus rooms with egress. 2 stall att garage and extra heated 3 stall garage with sauna. Cross country ski trails, ice rinks and one of our area gems, the Reif Performing Arts Center, are nearby. Take a look at the tour for a virtual walk thru of this gorgeous home.

description: For sale: $394,900. Very tastefully remodeled 4 BR home with 3792 total square feet, and a 3 stall attached heated & insulated garage. The house has a walk out basement, big south facing windows, a nice wood stove with glass door, new septic system, many custom built-ins made by Ken Stevens, oak wood floors,  large 4 stall garage with added work space and new everlasting roof. description: For sale: $189,900. Very unique family retreat on Johnson Lake. The main year-round home is one level living with 2 BR, 2 full baths & includes a master suite with walk-in closet. There's a built-in wood fireplace and wrap around deck. Included is the original log lodge which at 1738 sq ft has 2 BR, a large living room with stone fireplace, large rec area, dining area and original kitchen with wood stove. description: Recently sold: $128,000. This 3BR/3BA home is nestled on over 2.3 wooded acres with 283 feet of sand/rock lakeshore on one of Northern Minnesota's most renowned lakes. description:
Recently sold: $270,000. Gorgeous 3 bedroom (room for 4th bedroom) home located on 1.2 acres with beautiful views of Pokegama Lake, and has 187ft of beautiful sandy shoreline of Pokegama Lake. Pokegama Lake is a 6,500+ acre chain that connects to Jay Gould, Little Jay Gould, and the Mississippi River. There is a 2 car detached garage with lots of storage (800 sqft) and a large deck overlooking Pokegama Lake. The main level offers so much such as a nice sized kitchen with new floors, newer appliances, and a beautiful breakfast bar. The dining room offers new floors, and large windows overlooking the large yard on one side, and the lake on the other. The living area has plenty of room for the entire family with original wood floors, wood burning fireplace, surround sound and a sliding door leading out to the large deck to watch the sunrise and sunsets. The lower level has a large bedroom with space for a second bedroom (needs egress window) updated bathroom, a nice family room with a beautiful propane fireplace and has a walkout basement leading to the large fire pit that can seat multiple people! This Pokegama Lake home has 187ft of sandy shoreline and is only steps from the lake (has snowmobile ramp down to lake). The snowmobile ramp can be leveled for a use of a golf cart/four wheeler, or a nice, easy trail down to the lake. So seniors, no need to worry about the steps!! Pokegama Lake is perfect for fishing, boating, tubing, swimming, and even has many popular restaurants on the lake including the Pickled Loon Salloon, Zorbaz, and Pokegama Golf Course. The dock and boat lift are negotiable. Great for entertaining friends and family. Unbelievable price listed 40k under market value. Realtors welcome. Come for a private showing today. Don't miss out on this excellent opportunity! The square footage is to be determined by buyers or buyers agent. Serious buyers only

Call or Text (612) 293-0059 
Or Email forsalebyownerheather@gmail.com

description: Recently sold: $220,000. This beautiful home is situated on a corner lot beneath sprawling shade trees, in the historical district in Grand Rapids just a block from Crystal Lake. Enjoy the warm patina of the original maple floors, formal dining room and breakfast nook, sunroom, two fireplaces, sauna, and numerous modern updates - all while keeping the vintage charm this neighborhood is known for. The back yard is fully fenced and very private, the location is very desirable, and the square footage is wonderful - with tons of storage! The 2nd story has been converted into a kids play room and an office area, the lower level has a family room that can be finished off plus two bonus rooms, and there is also steps that lead to storage in the upper level of the garage. If you are tired of cookie-cutter houses the architectural features of this lovingly cared-for 3 BR are just what you are looking for!

description: Recently sold: $338,000. Unique property built in 2015, set on 74+ acres only minutes to Grand Rapids. Backed By The Golden Anniversary State Forest with trails throughout.

description: Recently sold: $420,000. Looking for your own slice of heaven on Pokegama Lake? 150 ft of gorgeous lakeshore located on a private road on Sherry's Arm. Sand beach, gradual drop off and beautiful views. Relax in your log, wood burning sauna just steps from the waters edge. Three bedroom traditional log home with welcoming front porch, vaulted ceiling, open loft, large bathroom with ball and claw tub, lower level bathroom with sauna/shower. Enjoy the lake views from the expansive sun room. Sunny northwest facing allows for sun most of the day and beautiful sunsets.  Extra large two stall detached garage features a full upper level for storage. Wrap around circle asphalt driveway. Pokegama lake is known for its clear water, boat to multiple eating establishments, golf, or travel up the chain of lakes, through Little Jay Gould, Jay Gould and into the Mississippi.

description:
For sale: $235,900. PRICE REDUCED
Completely remodeled, 3 Bed/2 bath home ideally located in one of the best Southwest neighborhoods. Close to several parks and miles of secluded walking and biking trails. You will be welcomed by the modern style that fills each room. The kitchen has brand new soft closing kitchen cabinets, granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, subway tile backsplash, black double sink, a large center island with a 9? overhang for additional seating, and high end modern light fixtures. All new Mohawk Rev Wood flooring, and Kichler Lighting throughout the main level.  The dining room offers plenty of room for seating along with a large sliding glass door to the beautiful stone patio perfect for grilling. The patio offers beautiful views of the neighborhood pond, along with a natural gas fire-pit for those beautiful summer evenings. The living room offers a beautiful wood burning fireplace perfect for those cold winter nights! 3 large freshly painted bedrooms with nice sized closets, new ceiling fans, and lighting. Don?t forget the completely remodeled, main level custom tiled bathroom and shower with all new lighting. The lower level offers plenty of space for those family fun games, and/or movie nights. The lower level also offers a nice 4th bedroom (Needs egress), with plenty of room for a 5th & 6th. A brand new ¾ bathroom. Other features include newer windows, new sidewalks, a brand new concrete driveway, attached garage, with an added man door to the garage. Baseboard heat with new covers throughout. This lot does have plenty of room to add another 1 or 2 stall garage. This is an opportunity you don?t want to miss! Don?t forget to watch out Virtual Home Tour in the link below!
Call or text (805) 405-5520 or text 218-208-4615

description: Recently sold: $230,000. Enter into serenity, tranquility and the smell of new construction.  This home is slab on grade on an efficient 50' South facing Mississippi River lot. description: Recently sold: $537,500. This beautiful 2 Story Pokegama lake home has so much to offer. 252' of shoreline, 4 BR/4 BA, perfect for entertaining with room for family and guests. Both formal dining room and breakfast nook off of the lovely kitchen. There is a family room on both first floor and lower walk-out level, each with a fireplace. Large master suite with walk-in closet and in-floor heat in the updated master bath. Ample storage throughout. Plus...a Bonus room over the 3 stall attached garage. The sun room views the perennial gardens and detailed landscaping leading to a hard sand beach. King's Point neighborhood is a desirable, almost self-contained community with members'-only facilities such as tennis courts, pickle ball courts, playground, boat launch and acres of land to enjoy - located on a private cul-de-sac. All this on the south edge of town convenient to golf, trail systems, shopping, medical services, and main routes of travel.

description: Recently sold: $285,000. What a great opportunity to own a fabulous home with end of the road privacy! huge Utility Room, and large Bedroom with large walk in closet. This home doesn't just capture quality, it captures a lifestyle balance of family
, comfort and luxury - within minutes of the hospital and town.

description: Recently sold: $330,000. Handscribed log cabin.

Recently sold: $299,000. This beautiful log-sided home is set on nearly 8 acres; private, yet minutes to town. This home includes 4 bedrooms, 2 3/4 baths with ceramic tile and custom built cabinetry, office area, open dining/ living room/ kitchen concept, family room, sauna, and 3-season sunroom/porch. The kitchen was remodeled in 2005 with custom hickory cabinets and all new appliances October 2015. Above the attached garage is situated the office area and master suite which includes a balcony, fireplace, walk-in closet, and bath with Jacuzzi tub. There are many closets and storage areas throughout the house. This home also includes an attached 2-stall in-floor heated garage with a work room and small kitchenette area, a separate 24 x 24 garage with a 10 foot overhang on side and back, and for the garden lover, a fenced-in 20' x 40' area to grow your favorite vegetables. The home and detached garage were re-shingled September 2015.
